{"title":"Bastion’s new Archetype ‘ultimate road bike’ goes aero plus wide clearance","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/bastion-archetype","date":1746165600000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/bastion-archetype\">Bastion’s new Archetype ‘ultimate road bike’ goes aero plus wide clearance</a></p>\n\n<p>High-end Australian brand Bastion Cycles has launched the Archetype, which it says is its first all-new bike platform in a decade and is their ‘ultimate road bike’.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As you’d expect, quite a bit has changed in <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/cycling-game-changer-tech\">bike design over the last ten years</a>. According to Bastion’s R&amp;D manager, Ethan York, ‘Our mission was to increase aerodynamic performance without compromising stiffness or weight. The Archetype achieves this with refined tube profiles and an ultra-efficient joining structure.’</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Archetype uses NACA aerofoil tube profiles. As with Bastion’s other bikes, including the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/bastion-road-disc-review\">Road Disc</a>, which we reviewed back in 2017, the tubes are filament-wound and held together by 3D printed titanium lugs. For more detail on Bastion’s unique mix of automotive engineering and 3D printing, which it used to produce custom components for the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cycling-australia-reveal-new-track-bike-components-to-rival-gbs-lotus-hope-bike\">Cycling Australia track bike</a>, see our <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/wizards-of-aus-inside-custom-bike-builder-bastion\">Bastion factory visit</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_007-970x647.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_007-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_007-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_007-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_007-1536x1025.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_007-2048x1366.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_007-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_007-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_007-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_007-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_007-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Archetype has Bastion’s 3D printed cockpit, while <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/are-wider-tyres-faster\">tyre clearance</a> is increased to 34mm – in line with modern trends – and Bastion has switched to a UDH rear derailleur hanger, opening up the option to fit SRAM full-mount groupsets such as the latest <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/sram-red-xplr-axs-groupset-review\">Red XPLR AXS</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/subscriptions?utm_source=Web&amp;utm_medium=Banner&amp;utm_campaign=Banner+3\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"300\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-3-970x300.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-3-970x300.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-3-300x93.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-3-768x238.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-3-1536x476.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-3-2048x634.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-3-750x232.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-3-1140x353.webp 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_014-970x647.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_014-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_014-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_014-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_014-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_014-2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_014-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_014-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_014-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_014-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/BASTION-ARCHETYPE-HR_014-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Other updates include replacing the 3D printed titanium head tube badge that Bastion previously used with a new 0.05mm thick logo etched from stainless steel. This is so thin that Bastion can place it under the frame’s surface coating, ensuring there’s no aero penalty.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/bastion-road-disc-review\">Bastion Road Disc review</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/bastion-launches-3d-printed-integrated-cockpit-system\">Bastion launches 3D printed integrated cockpit system</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cycling-australia-reveal-new-track-bike-components-to-rival-gbs-lotus-hope-bike\">Cycling Australia reveal new track bike components to rival GB’s Lotus-Hope bike</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/wizards-of-aus-inside-custom-bike-builder-bastion\">Wizards of Aus: Inside custom bike builder Bastion</a>\r\n                      